{"word":"σκοπιάζω","slug":"σκοπιάζω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>σκοπιάζω</b></el> <el>(σκοπιάζω,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:σκοπιά'><el>σκοπιά</el></a>\n<br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>only in <a href='S:present tense'>pres.</a> and <a href='S:imperfect tense'>imperf.</a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to look about one, spy from a high place</i> or <i>watchtower</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>: <i>to spy, explore</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:transitive'>trans.</a> <i>to spy out, search out, discover</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>:—so in <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a> <i>to look out for</i>, <b><a href='S:Theocritus'>Theocr.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}